## Key Conventions

- Read `.planning/CURRENT.md` before starting work.
- Check `.planning/DECISIONS.md` before proposing architecture changes (append-only — never delete).
- **Never invent** library API methods — always verify from `docs/external-apis/` or official docs.
- One logical change per commit: `<type>: <short description>` (feat/fix/refactor/test/docs/chore).

## Security

- Never write API keys, tokens, passwords, or secrets into code or commit messages.
- SQL via parameterized queries only — no string concatenation with user input.
- Flag auth, crypto, payments, or PII handling for review before committing.

## Definition of Done

All of the following must be true:
- [ ] `{{COMPILE_COMMAND}}` passes
- [ ] All tests pass (new tests added for changed behaviour)
- [ ] `{{LINT_COMMAND}}` passes
- [ ] No unexplained `TODO`/`FIXME`
- [ ] Committed to git
